    cons={[
      'Requires a little patience in early sessions.',
      'Needs a reliable scale and consistent puck prep.',
      'Roast changes still require fresh micro-adjustments.',
    ]}
  />

  <BuyingGuideSection>
    <h2>How grinder type changes your espresso settings workflow</h2>
    <p>Stepped grinders are easier for most beginners because each move is explicit and repeatable. Stepless grinders allow finer correction, which is useful when you are chasing narrow flavor windows. The right choice depends less on hype and more on your daily routine.</p>
    <p>If you rotate coffees often, low-retention designs reduce carryover and usually make setting changes feel cleaner. If you run one house blend daily, a simpler hopper workflow can be faster. Match workflow to habits, then optimize from there.</p>

    {tools.map((tool) => (
      <section>
